name: fodder yeast to generic market for protein feed | protein feed, 100% crude | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/3276/documentation

This is a linking activity that converts fodder yeast into protein, 100% crude for the feed market and gross energy for the feed market. ;The naming of the dataset is based on the feed nomenclature system of the National Research Council (USA).  Products with less than 20 percent of protein are classified as energy feeds. Products with more than 20 percent of protein are classified as protein feeds.

The activity starts with the reception of fodder yeast

The activity ends with the conversion of fodder yeast into crude protein and gross energy.
category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals

processDocumentation.samplingDescription: inventory based on gross energy and protein composition of raw material. Data obtained from Agroscope database of feedstuff compositions.

exchanges.description: Calculated based on crude protein content of fodder yeast (0.53 kg/kg dry mass). The dry mass of the reference product is 0.92kg/kg.
